
 Freyja 0.9.5
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 Freyja is a low polygon count 3d modler and animator.


 * Starting new feature listing here to be comprehensive, and this is of
   course incomplete.  Remove this line once it is complete...


 Animation

	* Object animation

	* Vertex animation

	* Skeletal animation

	* Forward kinematics

	* Autokeyframing


 Mesh editing

	* Basic polygonal mesh editing

	* Basic face exruding

	* Texcoord generation

	* Normal generation, flipping

	* Tesselation

	* Copy/Cut/Paste/Undo/Redo


 Plugins

	* NOD
	* MDL/MD2/MD3/MD5 ( Doom3 )
	* NIF4 ( Morrowind )
	* PSK/PSA
	* ...
	* SMD - Full import / export, fully save/load cycle safe
	* EGG - Full import / export, Eggv7 and Eggv8
	* JA  - Full import / export
	* ASE - Import / export, However doesn't use all 3ds features
	* OBJ - Import / export, No surface support
	* MDL - ( Halflife ) Import skeleton, mesh import disabled
	* MDL - ( Quake ) Import, export?, imports morph frames
	* MD2 - Import, imports morph frames
	* MD3 - Import/export, vertex morph frame import/export, no tags support
	* GLM - ( Jedi Knight II, etc ) Import, can 'guess' bones from glm mesh too
	* TR  - ( Tombraider 1-4 ) Import, disabled in current build
	* Others not listed yet



 DEVELOPER NOTES
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------


 Compiling for ATi systems
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1. Open freyja/Makefile

 2. Remove the line -DUSE_ARB_MULTITEXTURE -DOPENGL_EXT_MULTITEXTURE

 3. Remove the \ character at the end of the line above that one

 4. Rebuild


 Adding a new widget to mgtk ( Resource.cpp version )
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1. Add the new Gtk+ implemetation to mgtk_resource.cpp.  Remember you must
	take an 'arg' and pass an 'arg' back.

 2. Hookup any callbacks in mgtk_callbacks.cpp or mgtk_resource.cpp if wrapping.

 3. Add declaration of Gtk+ implementation function to Resource.cpp.

 4. Add an mlisp symbol to C function binding in Resource::Resource() using 
	RegisterFunction(...).


 SVN examples
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

	svn commit -m "Comment"

	svn co svn://svn.icculus.org/freyja/trunk freyja

	svn co svn+ssh://USERNAME@svn.icculus.org/public/freyja/trunk/ freyja





